    "created_at": "2017-03-03T20:57:48Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-03-03T20:57:48Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": ">As I said in the other issue, I wouldn't do this - I would subclass TerminalIPythonApp in rlipython and override init_shell there, so you start it with rlipython, not by configuring ipython.\r\n\r\nWhy weld something when it could be swappable? \r\n\r\nPlease consider why we're doing this in the first place: IPython 5.0 broke a bunch of people's workflows when it unilaterally moved away from readline to prompt toolkit without giving users the ability to fall back to old behavior. #10364 has a list of many of them, and proposed bringing back that code into IPython, which you (@takluyver) are strongly against. @Carreau is already making the compromise of not putting that code back into IPython, but instead proposes a straightforward ability for users who relied on the old behavior to install a package, set a config, and continue using IPython."
  },
